Step 2: Dilute to 100 mM Citric Acid

1. Draw 10 units (100 µL) of 1 M stock


2. Inject into 900 µL RO water


3. Mix well


4. Label: “100 mM Citric Acid”




---

Step 3: Dilute to 10 mM Citric Acid

1. Draw 10 units (100 µL) of 100 mM


2. Inject into 900 µL RO water


3. Mix well


4. Label: “10 mM Citric Acid (for titration)”




---

Step 4: Make 1 M Trisodium Citrate Stock

1. Weigh 294 mg trisodium citrate dihydrate


2. Add to 1.5–2 mL RO water


3. Mix until dissolved


4. Label: “1 M Trisodium Citrate”




---

Step 5: Dilute to 100 mM Trisodium Citrate

1. Draw 10 units (100 µL) of 1 M stock


2. Inject into 900 µL RO water


3. Mix well


4. Label: “100 mM Trisodium Citrate”




---

Step 6: Dilute to 10 mM Trisodium Citrate

1. Draw 10 units (100 µL) of 100 mM


2. Inject into 900 µL RO water


3. Mix well


4. Label: “10 mM Trisodium Citrate”




---

Step 7: Titrate and Finish Buffer

1. Combine your 10 mM Trisodium Citrate with ~80% final volume RO water
– Example: 800 µL trisodium citrate + 100 µL water


2. Slowly add 10 mM Citric Acid, a few µL at a time


3. Stir gently and check pH


4. Stop when pH is ~7.2


5. Add water to bring final volume to 1 mL if needed




